               <head>Romance of Amir Mukhtar Saqafi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Mukhtār'nāmah</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010112937 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002009961" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3716-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Anonymously written prose version of the romance of Amīr Abū Isḥāq Mukhtār ibn Abū ʿUbayd ibn Masʿūd al-S̲aqafī (d. 67/687), the ruler of Kufa, who challenged Umayyad and Zubayrid authority, while pursuing the named perpetrators of atrocities against Imām Abū ʿAbd Allāh al-Ḥusayn and his family
</p>
                        <p>The work lacks a preface or introduction
</p>
                        <p>Crude illuminated headpiece added later to opening, with outlined gold wash interlinear taḥrīr
</p>
                        <p>Dated at end: completed during the night of Wednesday, 19 Muḥarram 1278/27 July 1861, by Aṣghar ʿAlī Bayg known as Sangī Bayg, for his singular friend Mirzā Khudā Bakhsh Bayg Khān
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_917">Mukhtār'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_917">مختار نامه</title>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
